0.text: • Began to walk on two legs • Started to use simple stone tools, began to use fire • Built a shelter from large bones of animals • Lived in groups • Did not farm. Hunted and gathered food • Started using bows and arrows • Started to live in one place longer • Discovered metal, started to make tools • Started agriculture and rearing animals • Started to live in villages, built houses of wattle and daub • Had free time after harvesting, began to engage in dancing, music
